05391nam a22007815i 9783110703726DE-B159720210526051534.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210526t20202020gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2020939688  a97831107037267 a10.1515/97831107037262doi  a(DE-B1597)550325  a(OCoLC)1191863760  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE1 aFleischer, Kilian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Original Verses of Apollodorus’ ›Chronica‹ :bEdition, Translation and Commentary on the First Iambic Didactic Poem in the Light of New Evidence /cKilian Fleischer. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (XI, 303 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aSozomena ;v1900tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPraefatio -- tPart 1: Introduction -- t1 Overview of this monograph: motivation, scope and structure -- t2 The biography of Apollodorus of Athens -- t3 Apollodorus’ Chronica – Content, reception, book division, publication date(s), dedication -- t4 The Chronica as the first iambic didactic poem – innovation, metrical analysis, vocabulary and style, reception -- t5 The 109 original verses with new readings: History of the Academy and various other topics -- tPart 2: Edition with translation and commentary -- t6 Preface to the edition -- t7 Edition with translation -- t8 Commentary -- tPart 3: Diplomatic transcript and images -- t9 Diplomatic transcript with trace description, HSI, MSI and disegni (Index Academicorum) -- tPart 4: Index nominum et verborum -- t10 Index of the verses of the Chronica -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe Chronica by the grammarian Apollodorus of Athens (2nd century BC) was an exemplary chronographical reference work. It was composed in trimeters and represents the first Iambic didactic poem ever. So far, the surviving original verses have hardly been appreciated and analyzed in their own terms. Therefore a comprehensive collection of these verses is provided, including an introduction, edition, translation and commentary. Most verses stem from Philodemus' Index Academicorum, a Herculanean papyrus. Through the use of new imaging techniques and cutting-edge editing methods, enormous textual progress has been made. Many verses have been newly restored or significantly improved. They often reveal new hard facts about Academic philosophers and also bear some relevance for the dating of the Chronica and for Apollodorus' biography. In short, this collection guarantees easy access to the genuine verses of the Chronica, as originally drafted by Apollodorus, and thereby facilitates a contextualization or comparison with other (Iambic) didactic poems on a dramatically changed textual basis. The scope of the book fulfills various scholarly desiderata from a historical, philosophical, philological and literary-critical standpoint.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 4aAntike Historiographie. 4aAntikes Lehrgedicht. 4aChronographie. 4aPapyrologie.  aPapyrology, Chronography, Ancient didactic poetry, Ancient historiography.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2020z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020 Englishz978311070483908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020z9783110704631oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311070338240uhttps://doi.o